- 'labels of the topics' refers to 'tag names';
- 'Bob from the university' refers to the user with the email 'bob@university.edu';
- 'looked into by reviewing' means the user has reviewed publications related to these tags.

- "treasures" refers to the publications;
- "gleam in the eyes of the average user" metaphorically indicates the average number of downloads per user;
- "most mesmerizing to the least captivating" means sorted by average downloads in descending order.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) 
FROM downloads 
WHERE download_date >= date('now', 'start of month');
